<!--
VOICING PLAN:
Phrase 1 (mm. 1-4): Opening with light texture. Used "33" root triads and "333" 7th chords.
  LH carries D2 F#2 A2 D3 open voicing (root-3rd-5th-oct); RH lighter with just 5th+oct or 3rd+5th.
  m3 features passing harmonies on each beat (IV-V-IV-vii°7) for rhythmic interest.

Phrase 2 (mm. 5-8): Increased rhythmic variety. V7 chord in m6 uses "333" full voicing.
  m7 iii→V progression with "43" 1st inversion in RH for forward motion.
  m8 half-cadence on V "334" whole note — open, suspended sound before phrase 3.

Phrase 3 (mm. 9-12): 7th chords introduced. m9 uses IΔ and vi7 for richer color.
  m10 has V→Vsus4→I progression showing quartal "44" color.
  m11 IV→vii°7 creates anticipation. m12 full resolution.

Phrase 4 (mm. 13-16): Climax. m15 has IV-ii-V7-I progression with full 4-note LH chords.
  m16 final cadence: I "334" in RH, D1 pedal bass reinforces root position.
  All 8 SSAATTBB voices + pedal active in final measure.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
